Package space.sunqian.common.base.logging

Interface SimpleLogger

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractSimpleLogger
public interface SimpleLogger
A very simple logger interface, using SimpleLogger.Level to determine which messages can be output: only messages with higher or the same log level can be output.

  • Nested Class Summary

    Nested Classes
    Modifier and Type
    Interface
    Description
    static enum 
    SimpleLogger.Level
    Level of SimpleLogger, including: SimpleLogger.Level.FATAL, SimpleLogger.Level.ERROR, SimpleLogger.Level.WARN, SimpleLogger.Level.INFO, SimpleLogger.Level.DEBUG, and SimpleLogger.Level.TRACE, from highest to lowest level.

    • fatal

      void fatal(Object @Nonnull ... message)
      Logs the given message with SimpleLogger.Level.FATAL level. The message will be output on a single line in the order of the array, just like they are joined into one string. Using Object.toString() to convert the message object to string.
      Parameters:
      message - the given message
